# Supabase Environment Configuration

# Get these values from your Supabase project settings
# Project Settings > API > Project URL
SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_project_url_here

# Project Settings > API > Project API keys > anon public
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here

# Project Settings > API > Project API keys > service_role (optional, for admin operations)
SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY=your_supabase_service_role_key_here

# Instructions:
# 1. Create a new Supabase project at https://supabase.com
# 2. Go to Project Settings > API
# 3. Copy the Project URL and paste it as SUPABASE_URL
# 4. Copy the anon public key and paste it as SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
# 5. Run the SQL schema from database/supabase_schema.sql in your Supabase SQL Editor
# 6. Rename this file to .env and place it in the project root
# 7. The .env file is already in .gitignore so your credentials won't be committed

# Example (replace with your actual values):
# SUPABASE_URL=https://abcdefghijklmnop.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...